window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Don't miss one of America's top 100 most-loved novels, selected by PBS's <i>The Great American Read</i>.</p> <p>Four adventurous siblings - Peter, Susan, Edmund, and Lucy Pevensie - step through a wardrobe door and into the land of Narnia, a land frozen in eternal winter and enslaved by the power of the White Witch. But when almost all hope is lost, the return of the Great Lion, Aslan, signals a great change...and a great sacrifice.</p> <p><i>The Lion, the Witch, and the Wardrobe</i> is the second book in C. S. Lewis' classic fantasy series, which has been drawing readers and listeners of all ages into a magical land with unforgettable characters for over 60 years. This is a stand-alone listen, but if you would like to explore more of the Narnian realm, follow up with <i>The Horse and His Boy</i>, the third book in The Chronicles of Narnia.</p>"; 
